Jose Fernandez, a managing director
at  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS) â€™s prime brokerage, joined S3
Partners LLC, a provider of services to financial firms, as head
of business development.  Fernandez, 47, left Goldman Sachs in April, where he had
worked for 26 years and was responsible for co-managing the
prime-brokerage client services team in the U.S., New York-based
S3 Partners said today in a statement.  S3 Partners provides services and advice on counterparty
risk and financing costs to financial institutions, including
asset managers, banks, pension plans, insurance companies and
hedge funds. Fernandez will focus on getting new clients and
serving existing ones, Bob Sloan, managing partner of S3, said
yesterday in a telephone interview. Fernandez will report to
Sloan in  New York .  S3, which Sloan founded 10 years ago, advises clients with
more than $140 billion in assets, he said. Investment banks and
securities firms provide a range of prime-brokerage services to
hedge funds, including  securities lending , leveraged financing
and introductions to investors.  To contact the reporter on this story:
